2.1

  • Our goal is to minimize \(f(\theta)\) where \(\theta\) is a vector or a scalar

  • theta

  • here is the way to updata \(\theta\)

\[\theta{^{i+1}} \leftarrow \theta{^i}-\eta* \frac{\partial f(\theta{^i})}{\partial\theta^i} \]

  • \(i\) initail guess \(\eta\) \(\frac{\partial f(\theta{^i})}{\partial\theta^i}\)!

\(\theta\)dim \(\eta\) \[\frac{\partial f(\theta{^i})}{\partial\theta^i}\]

\(f(\theta)\)\(-\eta*\frac{\partial f(\theta{^i})}{\partial\theta^i}\)!

\(\theta{^i}-\eta* \frac{\partial f(\theta{^i})}{\partial\theta^i}\)

\(f(\theta{^{i+1}})\)

function \(y=f(x)=x^2\) theta in this case is x. intial guess \(x{^1}\) is -3. \(\eta=0.1\)

2.2

:\(\frac{\partial f(\theta{^i})}{\partial\theta^i}\)

\(2x{^{(i)}}\)

:

i=1

\[x{^2}=x{^1}-\eta*\frac{\partial f(x{^i})}{\partial x^i} \]

\[x{^2}=-3-0.1*2*(x{^1}) \] -3\(x{^1}\) \[x{^2}=-3-0.1*2*(-3) \] \[x{^2}=-2.4\]

i=2

-2.4\(x{^2}\)

\[x{^3}=-2.4-0.1*2*(-2.4)\] \[x{^3}=-1.92 \]

2.3 (1)

\(y=f(x)\)

$ min f(x)=x^2$x=0\(0\)

x=seq(-3,3,0.01)
plot(  x,x^2 ,type = "l" ,xlab = "x",ylab = "f(x)"  )

  • (Xf(x))
#R is number of iteration 
R=10
#eta is learning rate
eta <- 0.1
#intail guess of x
intail_x <- -3
# objective function
f <- function(x) {x^2}
# partial objective function
partialf <-function(x) {2*x} 

x=numeric(length=(R+1))
x[1] <-intail_x 

for(i in 1:R){

  x[i+1] <- x[i]-eta*partialf(x[i])
  
}
data.frame(x,y=f(x))

#intail guess of x

# objective function

# partial objective function
partialf <-function(x) {2*x}

2.4.1 case1:

\(\eta=0.0001\) - learning rate!

#R is number of iteration 
R=35
#eta is learning rate
eta <- 0.001
#intail guess of x
intail_x <- -3
# objective function
f <- function(x) {x^4-8*x^3}
# partial objective function
partialf <-function(x) {4*x^3-24*x^2} 
x=numeric(length=(R+1))
x[1] <-intail_x 
for(i in 1:R){
  x[i+1] <- x[i]-eta*partialf(x[i])
}
